-- RBS team says has 3.25 pct stake in ABN AMRO
-- 
-- Tue Aug 14, 2007 2:47am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/14/us-abn-amro-takeover-idUSWLB054820070814

 

 LONDON  (Reuters) - A consortium of European banks seeking to buy ABN AMRO AAH.AS said on Tuesday it had increased its stake in the Dutch bank to 3.25 percent. 

 The banks -- Royal Bank of Scotland ( RBS.L ), Spain's Santander ( SAN.MC ) and Belgian-Dutch group Fortis FOR.BR -- said they had bought 40.76 million ABN AMRO shares on Friday and Monday at an average price of 33.81 euros.